  "footnotes": [
    "The Olmec (c. 1500–400 BCE) are considered the 'mother culture' of Mesoamerica",
    "Teotihuacan (c. 100 BCE–550 CE) was the largest city in the pre-Columbian Americas with ~125,000 population",
    "The Aztec Triple Alliance (1428–1521) was conquered by Hernán Cortés with indigenous allies",
    "New Spain (1521–1821) was the largest Spanish colonial viceroyalty, governed from Mexico City",
